# Wayfinder Routing Standards

## NEVER Use Ziggy

**FORBIDDEN**: Do not use Ziggy's `route()` helper or any Ziggy imports.

```javascript
// ❌ NEVER - Ziggy legacy method
import { route } from 'ziggy-js';
route('posts.show', { post: 1 });

// ❌ NEVER - Legacy route() helper
<Link :href="route('posts.index')">Posts</Link>
```

## ALWAYS Use Wayfinder

Import from `@/actions/` (controllers) or `@/routes/` (named routes).

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Controller action imports (preferred)
import { index, show, store, update, destroy } from '@/actions/App/Http/Controllers/PostController';

// ✅ CORRECT - Named route imports
import posts from '@/routes/posts';
```

## Route Generation Best Practices

### 1. Controller Actions (Preferred)

Use named imports for tree-shaking optimization:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Named imports
import { show, update } from '@/actions/App/Http/Controllers/PostController';

show({ post: 1 });        // { url: '/posts/1', method: 'get' }
show.url({ post: 1 });    // '/posts/1'
update({ post: 1 });      // { url: '/posts/1', method: 'put' }

// ❌ WRONG - Default import (no tree-shaking)
import PostController from '@/actions/App/Http/Controllers/PostController';
PostController.show({ post: 1 });
```

### 2. Query Parameters

Always use the `query` object:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
index({ query: { page: 2, sort: 'created_at' } });
// Result: '/posts?page=2&sort=created_at'

// ❌ WRONG - Manual query string
index() + '?page=2&sort=created_at';
```

### 3. HTTP Method Awareness

Wayfinder knows the correct HTTP method for each route:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Automatic method detection
show({ post: 1 });    // GET /posts/1
store({});            // POST /posts
update({ post: 1 });  // PUT /posts/1
destroy({ post: 1 }); // DELETE /posts/1

// For specific methods:
show.get({ post: 1 });
update.patch({ post: 1 });
destroy.delete({ post: 1 });
```

## Inertia Integration

### Vue Links

```vue
<!-- ✅ CORRECT - Wayfinder with Inertia Link -->
<script setup>
import { Link } from '@inertiajs/vue3';
import { index, show } from '@/actions/App/Http/Controllers/PostController';
</script>

<template>
  <Link :href="index.url()">All Posts</Link>
  <Link :href="show.url({ post: post.id })">View Post</Link>
</template>

<!-- ❌ WRONG - Ziggy route() helper -->
<Link :href="route('posts.index')">Posts</Link>
```

### Vue Forms

Use `.form()` for automatic method spoofing (PUT/PATCH/DELETE):

```vue
<!-- ✅ CORRECT - Wayfinder form binding -->
<script setup>
import { Form } from '@inertiajs/vue3';
import { store, update } from '@/actions/App/Http/Controllers/PostController';

const props = defineProps<{ post?: Post }>();
</script>

<template>
  <!-- Create (POST) -->
  <Form v-bind="store.form()">
    <input name="title" type="text" />
    <button type="submit">Create</button>
  </Form>

  <!-- Update (PUT/PATCH) -->
  <Form v-bind="update.form({ post: props.post.id })">
    <input name="title" type="text" :value="props.post.title" />
    <button type="submit">Update</button>
  </Form>
</template>

<!-- ❌ WRONG - Manual action and method -->
<Form action="/posts" method="post">...</Form>
```

### TypeScript Form Types

Wayfinder generates types from Laravel Form Requests:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Type-safe form data
import { useForm } from '@inertiajs/vue3';
import { store } from '@/actions/App/Http/Controllers/PostController';
import type { StorePostRequest } from '@/wayfinder/types';

const form = useForm<StorePostRequest>({
  title: '',
  content: '',
  tags: [],
  meta: {
    description: ''
  }
});

// TypeScript validates all fields match the form request
form.post(store.url());

// ❌ WRONG - No type safety
const form = useForm({
  title: '',
  wrong_field: '' // Won't be caught
});
```

## Common Patterns

### Navigation with Parameters

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Route model binding
import { show } from '@/actions/App/Http/Controllers/PostController';

router.visit(show.url({ post: postId }));

// ✅ CORRECT - Multiple parameters
import { edit } from '@/actions/App/Http/Controllers/CommentController';

router.visit(edit.url({ post: postId, comment: commentId }));
```

### Prefetching Routes

```vue
<script setup>
import { show } from '@/actions/App/Http/Controllers/PostController';
</script>

<template>
  <!-- ✅ CORRECT - Prefetch with Wayfinder -->
  <Link :href="show.url({ post: post.id })" prefetch>
    {{ post.title }}
  </Link>
</template>
```

## Type Generation

After adding/modifying routes, controllers, or form requests:

```bash
# Auto-regenerates with Vite plugin (recommended)
yarn dev

# Or manually generate
php artisan wayfinder:generate --no-interaction
```

## Verification Checklist

Before committing frontend routing changes:

- [ ] All `route()` calls replaced with Wayfinder imports
- [ ] Using named imports from `@/actions/` or `@/routes/`
- [ ] Forms use `.form()` for method spoofing
- [ ] Type-safe parameters for route model binding
- [ ] Query parameters use `{ query: {...} }` object
- [ ] TypeScript compiles without routing errors

## Resources

- Wayfinder generates to: `resources/js/wayfinder/`
- Controller actions: `@/actions/App/Http/Controllers/`
- Named routes: `@/routes/`
- Type definitions: `@/wayfinder/types.d.ts`
